---
import MiFoto from "../../assets/img/MiFoto.png";
---

<!-- Main container -->
<div
  class="mx-auto mt-20 flex max-w-6xl flex-col items-center gap-8 px-6 lg:flex-row"
>
  <!-- Image -->
  <div
    class="border-primary h-64 w-64 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl shadow-lg md:h-96 md:w-96 drop-shadow-[4px_4px_0_#7836cf]"
  >
    <img
      src={MiFoto.src}
      alt="Photo of Paul Pop"
      class="h-full w-full object-cover"
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Text -->
  <div class="flex-1 text-center text-gray-300 lg:text-left">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">
      About <span class="text-white text-shadow">Me</span>
    </h2>

    <p class="mt-4">
      I’m <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Paul Pop</span>, a
      <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Unity Game Developer</span> with
      over <span class="text-primary font-semibold">7 years of professional experience</span>
      building and shipping games for
      <span class="text-primary font-semibold">mobile and PC platforms</span>.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-3">
      I specialize in designing and implementing
      <span class="text-primary font-semibold">gameplay systems</span>,
      <span class="text-primary font-semibold">performance optimization</span>,
      and <span class="text-primary font-semibold">scalable architectures</span>
      using <span class="text-primary italic">Unity Engine</span>.
      My work focuses on delivering smooth gameplay experiences, even on
      <span class="text-primary font-semibold">low-end mobile devices</span>.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-3">
      Throughout my career, I’ve led and contributed to multiple
      <span class="text-primary font-semibold">live commercial titles</span>,
      building features such as vehicle systems, customization system,
      mission frameworks, camera systems, runtime lighting solutions,
      and custom editor tools to improve team productivity.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-3">
      I’m particularly passionate about
      <span class="text-primary font-semibold">profiling, optimization, and technical problem-solving</span>,
      and I enjoy working on projects where performance, maintainability,
      and clean code matter as much as gameplay.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
